        <h3>Meaning of Colors</h3>
        <p style="font-weight: 100; line-height: 22px;"><span style="font-weight: 600; text-transform: capitalize; font-style: italic; color: #CC3E22;">RED:</span>
            Aggressive early game champions that rely on snowballing their lead. They have strong kill potential but fall off if they fail to secure early advantages.
        </p>
        <p style="font-weight: 100; line-height: 22px;"><span style="font-weight: 600; text-transform: capitalize; font-style: italic; color: #3cc89b;">GREEN:</span>
            These champions get stronger and stronger as the game goes on. They work well with their teammates and can win long fights by simply outlasting their opponents with their high stat growth or by enabling the stats of their carries.
        </p>
        <p style="font-weight: 100; line-height: 22px;"><span style="font-weight: 600; text-transform: capitalize; font-style: italic; color: #3c9bc8;">BLUE:</span>
            Strategic champions that focus on controlling the map and denying resources. They are weak early but scale incredibly well into the late game, requiring high map awareness and strategic thinking.
        </p>
        <p style="font-weight: 100; line-height: 22px;"><span style="font-weight: 600; text-transform: capitalize; font-style: italic; color: #FFFFFF;">WHITE:</span>
            Versatile champions that can fill multiple roles and support their team. They are resistant to early aggression and can adapt to any team composition.
        </p>
        <p style="font-weight: 100; line-height: 22px;"><span style="font-weight: 600; text-transform: capitalize; font-style: italic; color: #000000;">BLACK:</span>
            High risk, high reward champions that require certain conditions or sacrifices to unlock their full potential. They can accelerate a team's game plan but come with significant tradeoffs.
        </p>
